Package: makicoint
Type: Package
Title: Maki Cointegration Test with Multiple Structural Breaks
Version: 1.1.0
Date: 2026-03-09
Authors@R: c(
    person("Muhammad", "Alkhalaf", 
           email = "muhammedalkhalaf@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-2677-9246")))
Description: Implements the Maki (2012) <doi:10.1016/j.econmod.2012.04.022>
    cointegration test that allows for an unknown number of structural breaks.
    The test extends the Gregory-Hansen (1996) framework to multiple breaks,
    testing the null hypothesis of no cointegration against the alternative
    of cointegration with up to five structural breaks. Four model specifications
    are supported: level shift, level shift with trend, regime shift, and
    regime shift with trend. Critical values are provided for one to four
    regressors and one to five breaks.
